- I'll show you!

483
00:59:31,935 --> 00:59:33,425
Are you crazy?

484
00:59:35,738 --> 00:59:37,899
- Have you gone completely mad?
- Just wait, you'll see.

485
00:59:37,974 --> 00:59:39,839
- See what?
- You'll see.

486
00:59:40,477 --> 00:59:43,469
See what, Ben?
What am I supposed to see?

487
00:59:51,488 --> 00:59:53,251
It's not happening.

488
00:59:54,290 --> 00:59:56,087
It's not happening.

489
00:59:56,292 --> 00:59:59,090
Amy, I swear to you, at the Mayflower...

490
01:00:02,165 --> 01:00:04,030
I am not lying.

491
01:00:19,849 --> 01:00:22,943
Ben. Let's go back inside, okay?

492
01:00:26,489 --> 01:00:28,320
Put the gun away.

493
01:00:30,426 --> 01:00:33,862
Listen to me, baby. I want to help you.

494
01:00:34,330 --> 01:00:35,957
Tell the kids I'm sorry.

495
01:00:36,032 --> 01:00:37,260
Ben!

496
01:01:07,000 --> 01:01:12,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
No!

497
01:04:58,227 --> 01:04:59,785
Jesus Christ.

498
01:05:40,000 --> 01:05:45,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)

499
01:05:52,949 --> 01:05:54,974
Larry, it's me. I need your help again.

500
01:05:55,051 --> 01:05:58,612
I'm trying to locate the patient-employee
manifest for St. Matthew's Hospital.

501
01:05:58,688 --> 01:05:59,950
<i>Where is it?</i>

502
01:06:00,022 --> 01:06:02,217
Where was it? They closed it down.

503
01:06:02,291 --> 01:06:04,486
But it was in New York.
It's where the Mayflower used to be.

504
01:06:04,560 --> 01:06:06,653
<i>The Mayflower? The department store?</i>

505
01:06:06,729 --> 01:06:09,027
Do you have any idea where
they would store records for a hospital

506
01:06:09,098 --> 01:06:11,293
that's been closed for over 50 years?

507
01:06:11,367 --> 01:06:13,835
<i>No, I don't. But I can send someone
to city hall to check it out.</i>

508
01:06:13,903 --> 01:06:17,839
<i>If it's a public hospital, there'd be a record
of it. Tell me exactly what you need.</i>

509
01:06:17,907 --> 01:06:21,536
Same thing. I'm looking for a patient
or an employee with the name Esseker.

510
01:06:21,611 --> 01:06:26,207
<i>All right, I'm on it. Give me a couple hours,
and, Ben, keep your head down.</i>

511
01:06:49,105 --> 01:06:50,129
Hey.

512
01:06:50,206 --> 01:06:52,674
- Did you get it?
- Yeah, I think so.

513
01:06:53,476 --> 01:06:56,502
It's Anna Esseker.

514
01:06:58,180 --> 01:07:00,444
I didn't really know what you wanted,
so I got all the medical files.

515
01:07:00,516 --> 01:07:03,576
This is perfect, Larry. This is perfect.

516
01:07:03,653 --> 01:07:06,520
What happened?
Did you get in an accident?

517
01:07:06,589 --> 01:07:08,784
Anna Esseker's file,
did you have to go to city hall for it?

518
01:07:08,858 --> 01:07:10,257
No, I didn't have to go anywhere.

519
01:07:10,326 --> 01:07:13,295
All the files in that place were in storage
with the cold-case evidence.

520
01:07:13,362 --> 01:07:14,522
Why, because of the fire?

521
01:07:14,597 --> 01:07:18,260
No, it's before the fire.
It's a totally different case.

522
01:07:18,935 --> 01:07:20,596
Anna was a patient at St. Matthew's.

523
01:07:20,670 --> 01:07:23,298
She was in the psych ward
run by a Dr. Kane.

524
01:07:23,372 --> 01:07:26,500
Now get this,
she was only 12 years old when she died.

525
01:07:26,575 --> 01:07:27,564
What?

526
01:07:27,643 --> 01:07:31,602
When the nurses went on their rounds
first thing in the morning, October 6, 1952,

527
01:07:31,681 --> 01:07:34,673
they discovered that all the patients
had left their rooms during the night,

528
01:07:34,750 --> 01:07:36,741
and they'd all gathered in the main hall.

529
01:07:36,819 --> 01:07:39,413
Ben, they were all dead, including the girl.

530
01:07:39,488 --> 01:07:42,980
Apparently, they killed each other.
I mean, it was a slaughterhouse.

531
01:07:43,059 --> 01:07:45,425
That's when they closed the place down.
Who knows what really happened?

532
01:07:45,494 --> 01:07:47,860
- What about the doctor? Kane?
- Well, they arrested him.

533
01:07:47,930 --> 01:07:49,795
They found him dead
first day of the hearing.

534
01:07:49,865 --> 01:07:53,323
He slashed his wrists
with a piece of the cell mirror.

535
01:07:54,603 --> 01:07:57,265
- Thanks for your help.
- Good luck.

536
01:08:03,512 --> 01:08:04,740
Damn it!

537
01:08:41,617 --> 01:08:42,914
Jesus.

538
01:08:59,135 --> 01:09:00,796
"October 6, 1952."

539
01:09:05,274 --> 01:09:08,801
"Anna Esseker is diagnosed with
severe schizophrenia,

540
01:09:08,878 --> 01:09:13,178
"leading to withdrawal from reality,
delusional and violent behavior."

541
01:09:24,026 --> 01:09:26,654
"Pennsylvania, August 1951."

542
01:09:45,381 --> 01:09:46,848
They don't match.

543
01:09:49,085 --> 01:09:53,215
Anna Esseker was discharged
from St. Matthew's Hospital October 4.

544
01:09:53,289 --> 01:09:55,450
Two days before the massacre.

545
01:10:17,713 --> 01:10:19,943
She's alive, isn't she?

546
01:10:34,530 --> 01:10:37,897
You almost done, sweetie? Okay.

547
01:10:37,967 --> 01:10:42,404
Why is Daddy acting so scared?
It's not normal.

548
01:10:43,973 --> 01:10:46,771
He's way older than me.

549
01:10:47,343 --> 01:10:50,904
And I'm not acting scared, but he is.

550
01:10:52,181 --> 01:10:56,811
- Doesn't make any sense.
- Michael? What are you doing?

551
01:10:57,887 --> 01:10:59,081
Nothing.

552
01:10:59,922 --> 01:11:03,585
- Okay, well, we gotta get going, all right?
- Okay.

553
01:11:36,692 --> 01:11:39,183
<i>- Amy? Amy, what's wrong?
- Ben.</i>

554
01:11:39,261 --> 01:11:42,094
You have to come
to the house right now.

555
01:11:42,164 --> 01:11:43,756
I'm so scared.

556
01:11:43,832 --> 01:11:46,733
<i>- Amy, what's wrong?
- I'm so scared.</i>

557
01:11:46,802 --> 01:11:50,033
<i>- Amy, just tell me what happened.
- There's something in the house.</i>

558
01:11:51,607 --> 01:11:54,235
<i>- Something in the mirrors.
- I'm on my way.</i>

559
01:11:54,877 --> 01:11:56,367
God damn it!

560
01:12:02,818 --> 01:12:04,046
Come on.

561
01:12:54,770 --> 01:13:00,402
- Dad? When are you coming back home?
- Really soon, sweetheart. Come here.

562
01:13:03,712 --> 01:13:06,408
- I love you, Daddy.
- I love you, too, sweetheart.

563
01:13:06,482 --> 01:13:08,040
I gotta go.

564
01:13:08,550 --> 01:13:10,347
I'm afraid to stay here.

565
01:13:10,419 --> 01:13:12,387
There's gonna be windows and mirrors
wherever you go.

566
01:13:12,454 --> 01:13:14,888
Anything that causes a reflection
right now is dangerous.

567
01:13:14,957 --> 01:13:16,982
At least inside the house
we've covered everything.

568
01:13:17,059 --> 01:13:19,220
It's the safest place to be.

569
01:13:20,129 --> 01:13:21,255
Amy, I'm so sorry.

570
01:13:21,397 --> 01:13:24,855
No. It's not your fault.
I should've believed you.

571
01:13:26,602 --> 01:13:27,933
Come here.

572
01:13:31,874 --> 01:13:34,900
Ben, you do whatever it takes to end this.

573
01:13:36,078 --> 01:13:38,512
- You hear me?
- I will.

574
01:13:40,516 --> 01:13:42,313
I'll be right back.

575
01:15:37,966 --> 01:15:39,524
Jesus.

576
01:15:41,570 --> 01:15:43,094
Yes, sir?

577
01:15:43,172 --> 01:15:46,664
Excuse me. Is this the Esseker farm?

578
01:15:46,742 --> 01:15:49,438
- What is it, Jimmy?
- I don't know, Ma.

579
01:15:50,012 --> 01:15:54,176
- What can I do for you, sir?
- I'm looking for Anna. Anna Esseker.

580
01:15:54,883 --> 01:15:57,511
There's a man looking for...
You said Anna?

581
01:15:57,586 --> 01:15:59,213
Yes, Anna Esseker.

582
01:15:59,288 --> 01:16:01,222
An Anna Esseker, Ma.

583
01:16:02,991 --> 01:16:06,825
Look, I'm sorry to bother you.
I must have the wrong place.

584
01:16:08,330 --> 01:16:09,661
What is it you want with Anna Esseker?

585
01:16:17,573 --> 01:16:20,406
I'm doing a research paper
on schizophrenia.

586
01:16:20,476 --> 01:16:23,070
I became familiar with
Anna Esseker's case.

587
01:16:23,145 --> 01:16:25,477
I just wanted to ask her some questions.

588
01:16:26,915 --> 01:16:30,681
Go tell Grandpa there's a man here
who's asking about his sister.

589
01:16:30,752 --> 01:16:31,946
Okay.

590
01:16:32,588 --> 01:16:34,055
Thank you.

591
01:16:34,122 --> 01:16:35,419
Grandpa?

592
01:16:37,059 --> 01:16:39,254
You know, up to this day,

593
01:16:39,328 --> 01:16:42,729
visions of Anna's fits
still haunt me at night.

594
01:16:44,199 --> 01:16:49,102
I helped my father fix up this part
of the basement especially for her.

595
01:16:51,240 --> 01:16:53,208
Her fits were too violent.

596
01:16:53,275 --> 01:16:56,176
<i>My mother couldn't
take her screams anymore.</i>

597
01:17:04,386 --> 01:17:09,847
We had every priest, doctor, healer,
coming in from all over the county,

598
01:17:09,925 --> 01:17:11,893
but no one could help her.

599
01:17:25,440 --> 01:17:32,278
So finally, a Dr. Kane from New York
answered my parents' cries for help.

600
01:17:34,483 --> 01:17:38,419
He rejected the idea of demonic
possession, said he didn't believe in it.

601
01:17:38,487 --> 01:17:43,117
He was convinced Anna suffered from
a rare form of personality disorder

602
01:17:44,293 --> 01:17:46,659
and mirrors could help her.

603
01:17:47,563 --> 01:17:51,055
He wanted Anna under his care,
at St. Matthew's.

604
01:17:52,100 --> 01:17:54,227
My parents were very poor,

605
01:17:54,303 --> 01:17:57,704
but he agreed to cover all the costs
of the hospital.

606
01:17:58,240 --> 01:18:00,333
Where did she go after the hospital?

607
01:18:00,409 --> 01:18:01,808
Don't you know?

608
01:18:01,877 --> 01:18:04,505
She died there
with all of Kane's other patients.

609
01:18:04,580 --> 01:18:07,014
Mr. Esseker, I read the file.

610
01:18:07,082 --> 01:18:09,812
Anna left the hospital
two days before the massacre.

611
01:18:09,885 --> 01:18:13,377
Dr. Kane altered the documents
so she could disappear.

612
01:18:15,524 --> 01:18:17,048
Where did you get that document?

613
01:18:17,125 --> 01:18:20,583
I need you to tell me where she went
after St. Matthew's.

614
01:18:21,296 --> 01:18:23,662
She came back
and stayed with us for a while.

615
01:18:23,732 --> 01:18:27,998
What do you mean for a while?
What happened? Why did she leave?

616
01:18:28,070 --> 01:18:30,834
- I don't want to talk about that.
- Why did she leave?

617
01:18:32,341 --> 01:18:35,071
Because strange things
started to happen in the house.

618
01:18:35,143 --> 01:18:36,167
With Anna?

619
01:18:36,244 --> 01:18:39,702
No, no, not with Anna anymore.
No, she was totally cured.

620
01:18:41,750 --> 01:18:45,277
Strange things started to happen
with the mirrors, didn't they?

621
01:18:45,354 --> 01:18:48,653
Mr. Esseker, I need to know where Anna
is now. It's a matter of life and death.

622
01:18:48,724 --> 01:18:51,056
Do not make me threaten you.

623
01:18:51,126 --> 01:18:56,120
We sent her somewhere
where mirrors are forbidden.

624
01:18:57,199 --> 01:19:01,067
- Where the mirrors couldn't find her.
- Where? Where?

625
01:19:02,237 --> 01:19:05,604
St. Augustine's Monastery,
on the road to Reedfield.

626
01:20:08,203 --> 01:20:09,898
How can I help you?

627
01:20:11,339 --> 01:20:12,863
I'm sorry to disturb you, Sister,

628
01:20:12,941 --> 01:20:17,207
but I've come to speak with a member
of your community. Anna Esseker.

629
01:20:17,612 --> 01:20:19,671
Is she expecting you?

630
01:20:19,948 --> 01:20:21,245
No, not really.

631
01:20:21,316 --> 01:20:24,183
If you're not listed, I cannot help you, sir.

632
01:20:24,252 --> 01:20:28,348
Can you at least tell her
that I've come from New York

633
01:20:28,924 --> 01:20:30,448
to speak with her?

634
01:20:30,525 --> 01:20:33,790
I work with Dr. Kane
from St. Matthew's Hospital.

635
01:20:34,663 --> 01:20:36,858
It's very important, please.

636
01:20:42,771 --> 01:20:47,003
St. Matthew's closed down in 1952.
Who are you?

637
01:20:47,075 --> 01:20:49,236
My name is Benjamin Carson.

638
01:20:49,678 --> 01:20:53,478
I work as a night watchman
on Sixth Avenue in New York City

639
01:20:53,548 --> 01:20:56,847
in the building that used to be
St. Matthew's Hospital.

640
01:20:56,918 --> 01:20:59,478
What is it you want, Mr. Carson?

641
01:20:59,888 --> 01:21:01,753
My family is in danger,

642
01:21:01,823 --> 01:21:04,451
and what's threatening them
is asking for you.

643
01:21:04,526 --> 01:21:08,724
I came all this way to ask you

644
01:21:08,797 --> 01:21:11,027
why the mirrors that were left over
from St. Matthew's Hospital

645
01:21:11,099 --> 01:21:13,363
are so desperate to find you.

646
01:21:14,669 --> 01:21:16,398
Please, Miss Esseker.

647
01:21:17,038 --> 01:21:18,801
If you don't help me,

648
01:21:18,874 --> 01:21:21,206
I'm gonna lose the most important thing
to me in this world,

649
01:21:21,276 --> 01:21:22,971
and that's my family.

650
01:21:26,615 --> 01:21:28,549
Sit down, Mr. Carson.

651
01:21:37,626 --> 01:21:40,595
The mirrors are merely windows
on our world.

652
01:21:41,863 --> 01:21:44,730
It is not the wish of the mirrors to find me

653
01:21:45,801 --> 01:21:48,736
but of what is imprisoned inside them.

654
01:21:48,804 --> 01:21:50,897
What is imprisoned inside them?

655
01:21:52,274 --> 01:21:55,801
At the time that I was at St. Matthew's,

656
01:21:56,812 --> 01:22:00,407
<i>Dr. Kane's therapy
for personality disorders</i>

657
01:22:00,482 --> 01:22:05,351
<i>consisted of locking the patient up
in a mirrored room</i>

658
01:22:05,420 --> 01:22:11,586
<i>for several days on end,
forcing them to confront their own image.</i>

659
01:22:13,829 --> 01:22:17,060
<i>Dr. Kane was wrong about his theory.</i>

660
01:22:17,566 --> 01:22:21,263
<i>There is no cure for schizophrenia,
Mr. Carson.</i>

661
01:22:24,372 --> 01:22:26,806
It was something else.

662
01:22:27,475 --> 01:22:33,539
<i>And whatever it was,
it left me and entered the mirrors.</i>

663
01:22:35,417 --> 01:22:36,816
Since that day,

664
01:22:36,885 --> 01:22:40,480
it has been collecting
the souls of the people it kills.

665
01:22:41,523 --> 01:22:43,684
I'm sorry,

666
01:22:43,758 --> 01:22:47,091
but if I agree to go with you
and return back to that place,

667
01:22:47,162 --> 01:22:48,891
I will make it possible for the demon

668
01:22:48,964 --> 01:22:51,831
to cross the threshold
back into the real world.

669
01:22:51,933 --> 01:22:54,458
Do you understand
what that means for my family?

670
01:22:54,536 --> 01:22:57,664
You can't do this.
You need to come back with me.

671
01:22:58,506 --> 01:23:01,475
I'm going to pray for you and your family.

672
01:23:01,543 --> 01:23:05,104
That's all I can do right now, Mr. Carson.
I'm sorry.

673
01:23:06,681 --> 01:23:08,376
God bless you.

674
01:23:09,584 --> 01:23:14,817
Gary Lewis, Terrence Berry and many
other men have died trying to find you.

675
01:23:14,890 --> 01:23:17,085
And because they failed,
their families died, too.

676
01:23:17,158 --> 01:23:19,786
Two days ago my sister was murdered.

677
01:23:20,428 --> 01:23:23,454
My family will be next
if you don't help me.

678
01:23:23,899 --> 01:23:25,264
Please.

679
01:23:25,333 --> 01:23:28,564
Please. Wait, wait.

680
01:23:32,173 --> 01:23:33,606
This is my family.

681
01:23:33,675 --> 01:23:35,575
This is my wife Amy

682
01:23:35,644 --> 01:23:38,408
and my daughter Daisy
and my son Michael.

683
01:23:39,214 --> 01:23:40,909
They're beautiful.

684
01:23:41,383 --> 01:23:44,409
They're innocent.
They've never hurt anybody.

685
01:23:46,521 --> 01:23:47,954
Please.

686
01:23:48,290 --> 01:23:49,780
Take the photo.

687
01:23:51,293 --> 01:23:53,022
Just take the photo.

688
01:24:02,070 --> 01:24:03,560
Look at them.

689
01:24:06,574 --> 01:24:08,041
I'm sorry.

690
01:24:10,545 --> 01:24:13,013
Who the hell do you think you are?

691
01:24:13,281 --> 01:24:15,078
They're just kids!

692
01:24:53,188 --> 01:24:54,587
<i>- Hello?
- Amy.</i>

693
01:24:54,656 --> 01:24:57,250
<i>- Ben, where are you?
- At the monastery.</i>

694
01:24:57,726 --> 01:24:59,557
<i>- Did you find her?
- Yes.</i>

695
01:24:59,627 --> 01:25:01,652
Yeah? Did you talk to...

696
01:25:02,297 --> 01:25:04,424
<i>- Amy?
- Michael?</i>

697
01:25:06,101 --> 01:25:07,500
Michael?

698
01:25:07,736 --> 01:25:09,897
<i>Ben, hold on, Michael's gone.</i>

699
01:25:09,971 --> 01:25:11,233
- What do you mean?
- I don't know.

700
01:25:11,306 --> 01:25:13,706
I fell asleep with the kids on the bed
and now I don't know where he is.

701
01:25:13,775 --> 01:25:14,833
<i>Michael?</i>

702
01:25:14,909 --> 01:25:16,308
Amy, what's going on?
Is everything all right?

703
01:25:17,779 --> 01:25:18,837
Oh, fuck.

704
01:25:19,581 --> 01:25:21,139
Amy, what's going on?
Have you got Michael?

705
01:25:22,584 --> 01:25:23,812
Oh, my God.

706
01:25:24,686 --> 01:25:27,314
Ben, there's water everywhere.

707
01:25:28,356 --> 01:25:29,345
Oh, my God.

708
01:25:29,457 --> 01:25:33,154
<i>You've got to be careful of the water.
It creates reflections.</i>

709
01:25:33,962 --> 01:25:36,192
Someone is in the house.

710
01:25:36,264 --> 01:25:37,959
Someone scraped all the mirrors!

711
01:25:38,033 --> 01:25:39,625
Amy, where is Michael?

712
01:25:39,701 --> 01:25:42,363
I don't know. I don't know where he is.
I don't see him anywhere.

713
01:25:42,437 --> 01:25:44,268
<i>Amy, listen to me,
you've gotta stay away from the water.</i>

714
01:25:44,339 --> 01:25:47,069
<i>Get the kids
and stay away from the water!</i>

715
01:25:47,542 --> 01:25:49,635
<i>- Michael?
- Amy?</i>

716
01:25:49,711 --> 01:25:52,009
Amy? Shit!

717
01:26:00,722 --> 01:26:03,589
Which room is she in? Which one?

718
01:26:07,829 --> 01:26:10,525
My family is not dying tonight.
You are coming with me.

719
01:26:25,380 --> 01:26:26,574
Michael?

720
01:26:45,300 --> 01:26:46,528
Daisy?

721
01:26:49,604 --> 01:26:51,265
Daisy, come here.

722
01:27:05,286 --> 01:27:06,844
Come here, Daisy.

723
01:27:08,189 --> 01:27:09,247
Mom?

724
01:27:15,763 --> 01:27:17,230
Come here, sweetheart.

725
01:27:36,918 --> 01:27:38,818
What are you doing in there?

726
01:27:40,755 --> 01:27:43,087
Everything's going to be all right.

727
01:27:57,305 --> 01:27:58,863
No!

728
01:28:02,243 --> 01:28:04,677
No! No!

729
01:28:04,746 --> 01:28:05,906
Daisy!

730
01:28:08,983 --> 01:28:11,042
Come here! Get down!
Get down, right now!

731
01:28:11,119 --> 01:28:14,054
Get down, sweetie. Get down.
Oh, my God, are you okay?

732
01:28:14,122 --> 01:28:17,614
Oh, my God! Stay right there.
Don't move, baby! Don't move!

733
01:28:17,692 --> 01:28:20,126
- Mom, why did you do that to me?
- It wasn't me, sweetheart.

734
01:28:20,195 --> 01:28:22,129
You know I would never hurt you.
You know that.

735
01:28:22,197 --> 01:28:24,529
Here. Hold this. Hold it tight.

736
01:28:25,967 --> 01:28:26,991
Okay?

737
01:28:29,871 --> 01:28:33,238
Here, get down, sweetie.
Let me see. Let me see.

738
01:28:35,143 --> 01:28:37,373
Let me see, sweetie. It's gonna be okay.

739
01:28:37,445 --> 01:28:40,505
All right? I know it hurts. Stay right there.

740
01:28:42,584 --> 01:28:46,020
All right. Give me your hand.
I need you to hold it really tight, okay?

741
01:28:46,087 --> 01:28:48,612
Just flat and tight, just like that. Okay.

742
01:28:48,690 --> 01:28:51,989
Now, I need you to listen to me,
okay, baby?

743
01:28:52,060 --> 01:28:53,960
- You have to be very brave.
- Okay.

744
01:28:54,028 --> 01:28:55,825
I need you to stay here
no matter what happens.

745
01:28:55,897 --> 01:28:59,458
No matter what you hear. Do not move
from this closet until I come back.

746
01:28:59,534 --> 01:29:01,001
- You understand me, right?
- Yes.

747
01:29:01,069 --> 01:29:03,867
Okay. Okay.

748
01:29:03,938 --> 01:29:06,065
Do not move. I love you.

749
01:29:07,508 --> 01:29:08,634
Don't move.

